    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    This is a letter from William Edward Burghadt du Bois to Norman Leys. The letter has been written on a typewriter and is dated the 20th of October 1925. It concerns a review of the book "Kenya" for which The Crisis magazine will write a review. 
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            {EDITORIAL ROOMS OF}<lb/>
                            {THE CRISIS}<lb/>
                            {69 FIFTH AVENUE., NEW YORK, N. Y.}
                        </placeName>
                        <orgName key="Q502044">
                          {NATIONAL ASSOCIATION}<lb/>
                          {FOR THE}<lb/>
                          {ADVANCEMENT OF COLORED PEOPLE}
                        </orgName>
                        <persName key="Q158060">{W. E. BURGHARDT DU BOIS}</persName>
                        <date when="1925-10-20">
                            October 20, 1925.
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName key="Q7052495">Mr. Norman Leys</persName>,
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            Brailsford, Nr. Derby,
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            England.
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        My dear Mr. Leys:
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I am afraid your publisher is<lb/>
                    spoofing you. No copy of <title>"Kenya"</title> has<lb/>
                    been received by <orgName key="Q3520459">The crisis magazine</orgName>.<lb/>
                    However I have borrowed a copy from a<lb/>
                    friend and I am going to review it in<lb/>
                    a near number. I have nearly finished<lb/>
                    reading it and am greatly impressed<lb/>
                    by its importance and the hard work<lb/>
                    which you have done to gather the<lb/>
                    material<note><p>the letter t has been corrected, originally an e was typed here</p></note>. I do not know that you can<lb/>
                    hope for a very large circulation of<lb/>
                    the book in the United States, English<lb/>
                    books are so very costly. Nevertheless<lb/>
                    I wil give it such publicity as I can<lb/>
                    and certainly some sales<note><p>the letter l has been corrected, originally an i was typed here</p></note> ought to result.
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        very sincerely yours,
                    </salute>
                    <signed>W.E.B. Du Bois<note><p>Signature differs from the one listed on Wikidata</p></note></signed>
                    <seg>
                        WEBD/PF
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
